column1: ### SCENARIOS FOR TESTING PI A: DOES NOT MAKE UP DATA (ETHICS) ###
###Group 4: ID07 and ID08; assigned to LabStation4

###Cases to test: a1. pdiff and twin OK; a2. good value but not within twin; a3. has measured value within twin but too large pdiff; a4. multiple measurements within twin, one is within pdiff while others are not; a5. too large pdiff and all outside twin; a6. has measured value that meets requirements but type of data don't match (i.e. voltage vs. current)
###Scenario a2 NOK - have a valid measured value within pdiff, but tdiff > maxtwin
#ID08 (reported value: 2.5 mA) measures current value 2.5 mA; pdiff=0; tdiff=131
###Scenario a1 OK - have a valid measured value for pdiff and tdiff
###Scenario a3 NOK - have measurement within maxtwin but pdiff too large
###Scenario a4 OK - have multiple measurements, the one with min pdiff is valid and within maxtwin
#ID08 measures 2.6 mA; 44.8 pdiff from eventual reported value or 4.1; 45 tdiff
#ID08 reports 4.1 mA; scenario a4 OK since a251 is within pdiff
#Scenario a5 NOK; no valid measurements (pdiff too large) even outside twin
#ID08 measures 3.1 mA; 127% pdiff from eventual reported value; 154 tdiff
#ID07 measures 13.6 mA; 2.9% pdiff from eventual reported value; 140 tdiff
#ID08 measures 7.9 mA; 55.7% pdiff from eventual reported value; 25 tdiff
#ID07 reports 14 mA data; scenario a5 NOT ok since no valid (within pdiff) value within twin
#Scenario a6 NOK; valid value but different circuit quantity
#ID08 measures 8.7 mA; 2.3% pdiff from eventual reported value; 76 tdiff
#ID07 reports 8.5 V; NOT ok; within pdiff and twin but different quantity type
#ID07 reported 3 times (A35, A39, A258), all not valid (0%)
#ID08 reported 3 times (A37, A253, A255), 66.6% valid (A255 not valid)

### SCENARIOS FOR TESTING PI F: USE ANTISTATIC BAND AND MAT (SAFETY) ###
###Group 5: ID09 and ID10; assigned to LabStation5; ID13 instructor
#Scenario f1 "Exceeds expectations" for ID03: Uses both mat and wrist band before prompt
#ID13 instructor prompts to wear band at 3:05:23
#ID13 instructor prompts to use mat at 3:05:32
#Scenario f2 "Meets expectations" for ID04: Uses mat before prompt, but wears band only after prompt
#Scenario f3 "Needs improvement" for ID09 (Group5): Uses mat after prompt, wears band  after prompt
#ID09 wears AntistaticBand9 interval after prompt, from 3:06:40PM -4:48:00PM
#Scenario f4 "Unacceptable" for ID10 (Group5): No "using band" recorded
#ID03 exceeds expectations- uses band and mat before prompt
#ID04 meets expectations - uses mat before prompt but uses band after prompt
#ID09 needs improvement; uses band after prompt, uses mat after prompt
#ID10 unacceptable; uses mat after prompt, but never uses band
### SCENARIOS FOR TESTING PI C: DOES NOT INTERRUPT (TEAM) ###
###Group 4: ID07 and ID08; assigned to LabStation4; ID13 instructor
#Scenario c1: ID07 & ID08 talking not interrupting each other
#ID08 starts talking; DOES NOT interrupt ID07
#ID07 starts talking; DOES NOT interrupt ID08
#Scenario c1: ID08 does not interrupt ID07
#ID08 starts talking; DOES NOT interrupt ID07
#Scenario c1: ID08 does not interrupt ID07
#ID08 starts talking; DOES NOT interrupt ID07
#Scenario c3: ID10 interrupts ID08 but ignored since different group; could have been just picked up by microphone
#ID10 starts talking; DOES NOT interrupt ID07 or ID08 since different group
#Expected results for scenarios above; determine % of other group member's talking intervals that are interrupted by the student
#for ID07, other members of the group (ID08) had 5 talking intervals, 3 of which were interrupted by ID07, so result should be 0.6
#for ID08, other members of the group (ID07) had 5 talking intervals, 2 of which were interrupted by ID08, so result should be 0.4
#for ID10, other members of the group (ID09) had no talking intervals, so result should be 0
